KIND := Kubernetes Running In Docker 

- Refer the docs for installation setup of KIND on killercoda.com or any cloud platform 
Link :-
https://github.com/LondheShubham153/kubestarter/blob/main/kind-cluster/install.sh

------------------- File permission ---------------------------

- chmod 777 install_kind.sh

chmod 777 install_kind.sh is a Linux/Unix file permission command.

1️⃣ chmod

chmod stands for change mode.
It is used to change permissions of a file or directory.

2️⃣ 777

This number represents permissions for three groups:

Group	Number	Meaning
Owner	7	Read + Write + Execute
Group	7	Read + Write + Execute
Others	7	Read + Write + Execute

Then run the ./install_kind.sh file to complete the setup

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------- K8s Cluster Manifest file Setup ---------------------------

. Create dir /config -->> there create file -->> vim config.yml
. You can also refer the configuration file -->> https://github.com/LondheShubham153/kubestarter/blob/main/kind-cluster/kind-config.yml
. Everything in K8s is manifest file. 

kind: Cluster
apiVersion: kind.x-k8s.io/v1alpha4

nodes:
- role: control-plane
  image: kindest/node:v1.35.0
- role: worker
  image: kindest/node:v1.35.0
- role: worker
  image: kindest/node:v1.35.0
  extraPortMappings:
  - containerPort: 80
    hostPort: 80
    protocol: TCP
  - containerPort: 443
    hostPort: 443
    protocol: TCP

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------- KIND Cluster Creation ---------------------------

- Then Cluster Creation via KIND :-
kind create cluster --name=k8s-learning-cluster --config=config.yml

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------ Create Folder k8s_in_one_shot (Namespace, Pods, Deployement, Service) ----------------------

- Create k8s_in_one_shot dir there u will be creating the all mainfest files.

---------------------- Then create namespaces.yml file 

--> vim namespace.yml
--> 
kind: Namespace
apiVersion: v1
metadata:
  name: nginx-dev

- kubectl apply -f namespace.yml


---------------------- Then create pod.yml file 

--> vim pod.yml
-->
kind: Pod
apiVersion: v1
metadata:
  name: nginx-pod
  namespace: nginx-dev

spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.14.2
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80

- kubectl apply -f pod.yml
- kubectl delete -f pod.yml

If u want to debug the pod u can try this command and check what is runnning in pod :-
1. kubectl exec -it nginx-pod -n nginx (-n = namespace) -- bash 
2. kubectl describe pod/nginx-pod -n nginx-dev

------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------- Debugging Logs to check pods -----------------------
- kubectl describe pod/nginx-pod -n nginx-dev
------------------------------------------------------------

----------------------- Then create deployment.yml file

Before write any manifest file u can also confirm or check it on kubernetes offical docs like :-  kubernetes deployment

- Important :- What is Label and Selector
Label :- We will give label to every pod. (appName) 
Selector :- Selectors in a Deployment are used to match and manage pods whose labels match the specified criteria.

---> vim deployment.yml
--->
kind: Deployment
apiVersion: apps/v1
metadata: 
  name: nginx-deployment
  namespace: nginx-dev

spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector: 
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

// pod.yml file basically if u don't write separately u can also do it here as well (template and spec)
  template:
    metadata:
      name: nginx-dep-pod
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:                  
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:latest
        ports: 
        - containerPort: 80

---> Then run this command : kubectl apply -f deployment.yml

---> kubectl get deployment -n nginx-dev
NAME               READY   UP-TO-DATE   AVAILABLE   AGE
nginx-deployment   2/2     2            2           53s

---> Scale up or make the replicas of pod in specified deployment
---> kubectl scale deployment/nginx-deployment -n nginx-dev --replicas=5
------------------------------------------------------------


---------------- Deployment Rolling Update Command ---------------------------

. ReplicaSet -> bhi replication controller ko control krte ha.
. StatefulSet -> bhi replicas maintain krte ha. 
. Deployement -> bhi apke replicas maintain krte ha aur sath ma apke rolling update bhi maintain krte ha.


// Let suppose we want to update or shift to the previous nginx image version.
---> kubectl set image deployment/nginx-deployment -n nginx-dev nginx=1.27.3

// Here u can see the rolling update feature if u got the error still the previous images are running and the updates were sequentially affected.
---> kubectl get pods -n nginx-dev
NAME                                READY   STATUS         RESTARTS   AGE
nginx-deployment-59f86b59ff-5pjgk   1/1     Running        0          93s
nginx-deployment-59f86b59ff-v7fq9   1/1     Running        0          93s
nginx-deployment-849c87fc69-pjgd7   0/1     ErrImagePull   0          12s

------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------- Replica Set (Optional) --------------------------------

. In deployment we can update, scale or can do rolling update things but in replicaset we can't do these things that's why deployment is too flexible.

---> vim replicaset.yml
---> 
kind: ReplicaSet
apiVersion: apps/v1
metadata: 
  name: nginx-replicasets
  namespace: nginx-dev

spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  template:
    metadata:
        name: nginx-rep-pod
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80

. Then run kubectl apply -f replicaset.yml

------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------- Daemon Set (Optional) ---------------------------------

. Ensure krta ha har node pr ak replica chalta rahe.
. Command :- to know which pod is assign on which node.

root@controlplane:~/k8s_cluster$ kubectl get pods -n nginx-dev -o wide
NAME                                READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE   IP            NODE                           NOMINATED NODE   READINESS GATES
nginx-deployment-74dfc97b57-btl8v   1/1     Running   0          18s   10.244.1.9    k8s-learning-cluster-worker2   <none>           <none>
nginx-deployment-74dfc97b57-s6msp   1/1     Running   0          18s   10.244.1.10   k8s-learning-cluster-worker2   <none>           <none>

---> vim daemonset.yml
--->
kind: DaemonSet
apiVersion: apps/v1
metadata: 
  name: nginx-daemonsets
  namespace: nginx-dev

spec:
  selector: 
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  template:
    metadata:
        name: nginx-dmn-pod
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:                  
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:latest
        ports: 
        - containerPort: 80

