-------------------------- Jobs --------------------------------

---> vim job.yml
--->
kind: Job
apiVersion: batch/v1
metadata:
  name: job-demo
  namespace: nginx-dev
 
spec:
  # How many times u need to run this job 
  completions: 1
  # How many parallel node or server u need to execute the job
  parallelism: 1

  # pod template creation
  template: 
    metadata: 
      name: job-pod-demo
      labels:
        app: batch-task
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: batch-container
        image: busybox:latest    # busybox work is just only running the command
        command: ["sh", "-c", "echo Hello World Program && sleep 10"] # shell command to print statement 
      restartPolicy: Never

----> 

Run the command :- kubectl apply -f job.yml

Command to see thier executed logs performed in the job :- 
- kubectl logs pods/job-demo-gps2z -n nginx-dev

------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------- Cron Jobs --------------------------------

. Website to set the cron-job scheduling time :- https://crontab.guru/

---> vim cron-job.yml
--->
kind: CronJob
apiVersion: batch/v1
metadata:
  name: minute-backup
  namespace: nginx-dev

spec:
  schedule: "* * * * *"
  # jobTemplate means one single task template
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        metadata:
          name: minute-backup
          labels:
            app: minute-backup

    # jobTemplate container
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: backup-container
            image: busybox
            command: 
            - sh
            - -c
            - >
              echo "Backup Started" ;
              mkdir -p /backups &&
              mkdir -p /demo-data &&
              cp -r /demo-data /backups &&
              echo "Backup Completed!" ;

        # and whenever you assign data to your container so u need volume for it  
            volumeMounts:
            - name: data-volume
              mountPath: /demo-data
            - name: backup-volume
              mountPath: /backups
        restartPolicy: OnFailure    # if pod fails so restart then only.          
        volumes:
          - name: data-volume
            hostPath:
              path: /demo-data
              type: DirectoryOrCreate  # if the job doesn't able to find the relevant directory /demo-data so they will create it  
          - name: backup-volume
            hostPath:
              path: /backups
              type: DirectoryOrCreate

---> Then run the command kubectl apply -f cron-job.yml
---> root@controlplane:~/k8s-cluster$ kubectl logs pod/minute-backup-29623482-dqbht -n nginx-dev
Backup Started
Backup Completed!

------------------------------------------------------------